    "ai_summary": "# MONTHLY ATTRIBUTION REPORT \u2013 JUNE 2026\n\n## KEY FINDINGS\n\nTraffic grew 8.7% MoM (11,019 vs 10,139 sessions), but **pipeline collapsed 42%** ($19,777 vs $34,302) and deals dropped 13% (61 vs 70). We converted fewer visitors into revenue despite higher volume\u2014a clear efficiency problem.\n\nDirect traffic still dominates at 58% of sessions but shows severe engagement issues: **71% bounce rate, 1m40s session duration**. This screams bot traffic or misattributed sessions. Meanwhile, Organic Search (27% of traffic) demonstrates real intent: 32% bounce, 4m05s engagement, and delivered 13 deals worth $4,419. Referral traffic, though small (568 sessions), shows exceptional quality: 24% bounce, 5m35s duration\u2014but only 1 deal. We're not capitalizing on warm introductions.\n\nSearch Console reveals a **critical organic growth failure**: 1,216 clicks, 100% branded (vs 100% in May). We have zero unbranded visibility. Every search visitor already knows Privy exists. We're capturing demand, not creating it. The top non-branded opportunity doesn't exist in our data\u2014we're invisible to investors searching for \"real estate comps,\" \"fix and flip software,\" or \"investment property analysis.\"\n\nThe /pricing/ page mystery deepens: 278 sessions, **0 conversions, 0 deals**. Either our pricing turns people away, the page has tracking issues, or visitors who land there aren't qualified. The 0.2% homepage conversion rate (12 conversions from 5,373 sessions) suggests massive leakage in our acquisition-to-conversion funnel.\n\nHubSpot data integrity is compromised: all deals show 0 days to close and \"Closed Won\" status. This makes pipeline velocity analysis impossible and suggests deals are being manually backdated or improperly staged.\n\n## RED FLAGS\n\n**Pipeline quality deterioration**: Average deal value dropped to $324 (vs $490 in May)\u2014a 34% decline. Direct Traffic deals fell to $275 average while Offline sources jumped to $499. This inversion suggests our digital channels are attracting lower-value customers or we're closing smaller deals faster to hit volume targets.\n\n**The \"(not set)\" region shows 2,256 sessions**\u201420% of total traffic with no geographic data. Combined with Iowa anomalies from prior months, this indicates persistent tracking failures or significant bot contamination inflating our metrics while depressing our conversion rates.\n\n**Email marketing generated zero deals** despite 236 sessions and 33% bounce rate. With a 91-contact survey cohort sitting unused, we're leaving qualified pipeline on the table. Email should be our highest-intent channel.\n\n## TOP 3 ACTIONS THIS MONTH\n\n**1. Emergency Direct Traffic Audit (Week 1)**: Implement UTM parameters on all owned properties, newsletter links, and product emails. Install bot detection (Cloudflare/DataDome). Separate app.privy.pro traffic entirely from marketing analytics. Goal: reduce Direct attribution from 58% to <30% and expose true source performance.\n\n**2. Launch Unbranded SEO Content Play (Start Week 2)**: Create 8 bottom-funnel content pieces targeting \"comparative market analysis tools,\" \"real estate investment calculator,\" \"fix and flip analysis software.\" Target 200 unbranded clicks by July 31. Current 0% unbranded traffic is unsustainable\u2014we're entirely dependent on existing brand awareness.\n\n**3. Pricing Page Conversion Intervention (Week 2)**: A/B test pricing page with: (a) lead capture form before pricing reveal, (b) ROI calculator showing deal savings, (c) calendar booking CTA. Deploy heatmaps and session recordings. If no lift in 2 weeks, remove pricing from nav and gate it behind email signup. The 278-session, 0-conversion rate is killing pipeline.",
