    "ai_summary": "# Attribution Report: May 2026\n\n## Key Findings\n\nMay delivered **70 deals worth $34,302** \u2014 a 15% deal increase and 73% pipeline jump vs. June. Direct Traffic still dominates with 31 deals ($15,034), but Organic Search closed the gap significantly at 24 deals ($12,214). This represents a healthier distribution than previous months where Direct was essentially the only game.\n\nTraffic quality tells two stories. Email (157 sessions, 7m34s avg engagement, 33% bounce) and Referral (576 sessions, 6m54s avg, 35% bounce) traffic show strong intent signals but **zero attributed deals**. Meanwhile, Direct traffic converted 31 deals despite a 67% bounce rate and 2m36s engagement \u2014 suggesting attribution is broken or these users are completing signup flows outside tracked sessions.\n\nSearch remains a red flag: **100% branded, 1,143 clicks, zero unbranded discovery**. We're invisible to investors who don't already know us. \"Privy\" ranks at position 5.9 while \"privy real estate\" owns position 1.0 \u2014 basic brand term optimization would capture low-hanging fruit.\n\nThe pricing page mystery persists: **330 sessions, 0 conversions**. Either the tracking is busted or we're losing qualified traffic at the critical decision point.\n\n## Red Flags\n\n**Data integrity is eroding trust in this dashboard.** HubSpot shows 0 days to close across all 70 deals \u2014 impossible unless every deal was created and closed same-day. The \"(not set)\" region showing 2,547 sessions (25% of traffic) suggests GA4 implementation gaps. Login pages showing 105.6% conversion rate indicates double-firing or misconfigured event tracking.\n\n**Email marketing generated zero deals** despite having 157 engaged sessions (7m34s dwell time proves quality). The 91-contact survey cohort mentioned in context hasn't deployed \u2014 that's $18-27K in potential pipeline sitting idle based on current email-to-deal conversion benchmarks from other B2B SaaS.\n\n**Organic search stagnation**: 2,616 sessions from search, but literally 0 unbranded clicks means we're capturing zero demand from \"real estate investor software,\" \"flip analysis tool,\" or any problem-based queries. Competitors own that discovery layer entirely.\n\n## Top 3 Actions This Month\n\n**1. Fix attribution tracking before June data compounds the problem.** HubSpot's \"0 days to close\" across 70 deals makes pipeline forecasting impossible. Audit UTM parameters on Email/Referral channels specifically \u2014 both show strong engagement but zero deal attribution, suggesting broken source tracking. This is a 2-day engineering task that's currently costing us visibility into ~$10K+ monthly pipeline.\n\n**2. Deploy the 91-contact email survey cohort immediately.** Email traffic converts at higher intent (7m34s engagement) but we've generated 0 deals. At 10% conversion, that's 9 deals worth ~$4,400 in pipeline sitting untouched. If there's a reason not to deploy, kill the cohort and reallocate resources.\n\n**3. Launch unbranded SEO content targeting 3 buyer-intent queries.** \"Real estate investment analysis,\" \"fix and flip calculator,\" and \"rental property ROI calculator\" \u2014 publish one optimized landing page per query by June 15. Current state (100% branded search) means every organic deal already knew about Privy. Unbranded capture could add 15-20% to organic deal flow within 60 days.",
